    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">Office of <persName>ALLEN &amp; CO.</persName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>82 BEAVER STREET</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>NEW YORK</placeName>, <date>Mch 16 1865</date></p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. I Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir and friend</p>
            <p>Yours is at hand, and I should have written you earlier, had it not<lb/> been for the
                uncertainty in regard to<lb/> stopping the <add>Hebrew</add>. <add>?</add>
                <persName>Van Vlick</persName><lb/> will let me know on <date>Monday</date> if
                I<lb/> can ship on the “Arage” which sails<lb/>
                <date>Wednesday</date>. I telegraphed to you to<lb/> ship them to morrow per
                    <persName>C J A K</persName>
                <add>?</add>.<lb/> You can do as you think proper as<lb/> to paying freight. Please
                however make<lb/> a contract for shipping the same. Please<lb/> mark the
                    <sic>Boxes</sic>
                <hi rend="underline"><date>Passover</date> Bread</hi><lb/> B <placeName>Savannah
                    Geo</placeName><add>?</add>, and consign to<lb/>
                <persName>Allen &amp; Co</persName>
                <placeName>NY</placeName>, and send a Bill<lb/> of Lading. I think this is all I
                have<lb/> to say at present in regard to the matter.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With best regards very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M. M. Allen</persName>.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
